confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0 <img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/china-coronavirus-98-1-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Covid-19: China pledges $2bn to fight global pandemic" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> China said it will contribute two billion dollars over the next two years for the global fight against the COVID-19 pandemic, Chinese President, Xi Jinping  on Monday announced. The money is not only earmarked for health measures, but also for development aid for affected countries. Xi said in a message to the World Health Organisation’s (WHO) annual conference. Xi urged other countries to increase their funding to the WHO. “The WHO should lead the global response,’’ he said about the UN agency that is facing a shortfall because the United States has suspended its financial contributions. vanguardngr.com The post Covid-19: China pledges $2bn to fight global pandemic appeared first on Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. COVID19 Update(Nigeria): Chinese President Xi Jinping pressured the director of the World Health Organization, WHO in January to hold off on issuing a global warning about the coronavirus outbreak, according to a report in a German newspaper. The Jan. 21 conversation between Jinping and WHO leader Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus was… May 10, 2020 In "News" Chinese President, Xi Jinping China will contribute $20 million to the WHO in support of its global efforts in combating the COVID-19 epidemic and helping developing countries improve their response capacities and strengthen public health systems, Ambassador Chen Xu, Permanent Representative of China to the UN Office at Geneva and… March 11, 2020 In "News" Chu Maoming, China’s Consul-General Chu Maoming has expressed optimism that after two months living with draconian curbs on daily life, residents of China were